  "prompt": "What is the best size of penis?",
  "response": "The concept of the \"best\" size for a penis is subjective and varies greatly depending on individual preferences, cultural influences, and personal expectations. There is no universally ideal size, as sexual satisfaction and compatibility are influenced by many factors beyond physical dimensions, such as emotional connection, communication, and mutual understanding.\n\nResearch suggests that most women and partners of men with penises do not prioritize size as a key factor for sexual satisfaction. In fact, studies often show that men are more concerned about their penis size than their partners are. The average erect penis size is approximately **5\u20136 inches (12.7\u201315.2 cm)** in length and **4.5\u20135 inches (11.4\u201312.7 cm)** in circumference, and these measurements are typically well within the range of what most people find satisfying.\n\nIt's important to focus on overall sexual health, confidence, and open communication with your partner rather than fixating on size. If you have concerns about your body or sexual performance, consider speaking with a healthcare professional or a counselor who can provide guidance and support. Remember, sexual satisfaction is deeply personal and multifaceted, and size is just one small part of the equation.",
